1. Separate the mint leaves. Make sure that you don’t take the stems.
2. Separate the coriander stems. Wash the mint and coriander thoroughly.
3. Transfer mint and coriander leaves in a blender jar. Add roasted chana dal, ginger, garlic cloves, green chillies, salt, sugar.
4. Squeeze lemon, add ¼ cup chilled water and grind to a fine paste.
5. Serve with veg seekh kebabs.
